That’s right… the 3rd Annual Fxck Cancer Charity Golf Invitational is a go for 2021!
This year, we’re bringing the much anticipated event to the Strawberry Farms Golf Club in Irvine, CA on Wednesday, October 6th.  Registration is now open just use the link in our bio, get your foursome together and register ASAP… this event always sells out quick!
Special thanks to all our incredible sponsors that help make this event the huge success that it is and to all our supporters🙌🏼.
.
.

node.text: Implemented in 2011, Dyin 2 Live Dreams is a wish-granting program committed to helping those who are currently in the fight against cancer by giving them a one-of-a-kind “VIP Experience” that may be a source of hope, joy, and inspiration while they continue in their fight against these terrible diseases. Through our extensive network of friends, supporters, and partners, we put together our VIP Experiences, focusing on select music festivals, concerts, and sporting events throughout the year. We take our Dyin 2 Live Dreams recipients backstage and behind the scenes at these events to meet their favorite bands, artists, athletes, and celebrities. Meet-and-greets, signings, watching their favorite bands side stage, backstage access, media interviews, photo ops, and more are all apart of the VIP Experience! Our Dyin 2 Live Dreams recipients walk away from the experience with the will and determination to continue in their fight against cancer. We want to show them that life is worth fighting for and that no one fights alone.

node.text:
#TOGETHERWEFIGHT and today we ask you all to please surround fighter Rick Hallman and his family with all the love and prayers you’ve got as he is battling colorectal cancer🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽. He is a Hero to many and the definition of a warrior. As he would do for others and always stop to help those in need of rescuing we ask to please help him with your positive prayers and all your support. Rick we are all behind you in your fight and in your corner and today louder than ever we are screaming #FXCKCANCER for you and your family 🙏🏽🙏🏽. Please send your love and prayers to Rick in the comments below and here are some words from his sister Rebecca.

“This is my brother is Rick Hallman from Ithaca, MI. He is a firefighter, paramedic and 911 dispatcher, he has been battling stage 4 colorectal cancer and has been placed on Hospice care and being told he has days to weeks. He is going downhill fast, we would love your support for him and his family. He is a husband and father of 4 and he is a hero in many ways. He survived an ambulance accident while working in October 2017 which left him with a broken back and arm, he fought back and didn't stop the job he loves. Even while battling cancer it didn't stop him from helping others, if it was stopping for a car accident while out shopping or going on fire and Rescue calls. He is a hero to our family. When he was diagnosed my dad also went to get checked and we found out my dad had colon cancer as well but luckily he was able to have surgery and beat it. Rick saved our dads life! While we wished Rick could beat this too God had other plans for him :( he is fading fast and our family is heartbroken he put up one hell of a fight.”
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER #coloncancer

node.text:
Today’s #FCWarriorWednesday we rally around Shweta LoVoi in positivity & prayer as she goes to battle with Ovarian Cancer. Shweta know that you have the entire FC community of cancer fighters, survivors & supporters in your corner cheering you on & sending you strength to beat this🙌🏼. Stay motivated & strong & #KEEPFIGHTING . Please send our girl encouraging words and love in the comments below 

“I started noticing a mild pain on my right side of stomach & decided to go to a walk-in clinic where I was advised to get a ultrasound. Ultrasound found a cyst on my right ovary(9cm) & I was rushed to see a gynecologist. Upon doing another set of ultrasounds at the gynecologist's office it was later found to be a 4 cm cyst instead. Did a CA125 blood test only to find out that it was very high, so I was referred to an gynecologist oncologist for cyst removal. I was told time & time again that because of my age & no family history it won't be Ovarian Cancer & that CA-125 can be high for many other reasons. They were all wrong. I went in to a surgery for a cyst removal and came out as a ovarian cancer patient. 
Thankfully we found it early, which is quite a feat of it's own. I was diagnosed with stage 1c OVCA. 
I am currency going through chemo which is turning out to be a misadventure of its own right. So far, I have had reactions to both Taxol and Doxil, both included Blisters in the eyeballs, yes, you read that right, among other things. So, we are doing only carboplatin regiment with immunotherapy. I am hoping & praying that it works and we kick cancer's ass! Cause this 36 YO have bigger plans than OVCA. It has been quite surreal. 
Among all the tears and mental health issues, I have found my true friends. People I thought I would never speak again have come out to cheer for me and made themselves available 24/7. These last few months I have met so many fellow survivors who gave me hope during some very dark & hard times & I am eternally greatful for that. Especially since the average of age of OVCA is 63 and most don't have online presence. So, it's very easy to feel alone! And of course thank you #fxckcancer for providing the online support during this time. ❤️”

node.text:
Today’s #FCTattooTuesday we are honored to share cancer survivor Jerry’s art piece with you and champion him on beating cancer!!🙌🏼 We appreciate you sharing your words of encouragement and motivation for others in the fight. Your positivity is exactly what the world needs and you are providing light for others that may be in a dark place. Thank you🙏🏽🤍. Please send love to our man in the comments below and here is his story.

“I was caught off guard with stage 3 colon cancer at the age of 37(growing in me 3 to 5 years they said) no family history or anything. Talk about a silent killer and eye-opening event. I have beat it but 1 thing I know is that I'm mentally stronger more than I ever was. I know it's easier said than done but you just take one day at a time, allow yourself to have a down day here or there but always know that the next day will be better. The best thing I did was joke about it and some situations through it all and it helps keep the spirit up. Positivity is best!!!!”
.
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER #survivor

Today’s #FCMerchMonday is a exciting one featuring our “Together We Fight” unisex tee to let all warriors know we are in this with them are and supporting them through their battle💪🏽.

No one fights alone in this #FCFamily  and we appreciate your help in sharing our mission of awareness and resources to help prevent cancer with early detection 🙏🏽. 

Click the link in bio to learn more about how your purchases help fund our programs that benefit those in their fight through the #FCcancerfoundation and #Dying2livedreams and sign up for our newsletter for an extra 10% off all purchases to help support the cause and to stay informed🙌🏼
.
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER

node.text:
#FCSurvivorSunday goes out to our friend and cancer fighter Jason Carroll.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Jason you are such an inspiration with your passion for life and adventure, your will to fight and to continue live everyday to the fullest🙌🏼. We want to rally around you in positive thoughts and prayer that you will kick cancers ass a second time around and that your scans remain clear in the next few months so that you can get back to your track of remission🙏🏽🙏🏽. We know that you won’t let anything get in your way of LIVING and amazing life and we are excited to continue to watch and vicariously live through all your upcoming adventures. Please send positive prayers to our man Jason and words of encouragement in the comments below.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“2 years ago I was diagnosed with Non-Hodgkin's Lymphoma Large Cell B Stage 4, I won that fight and have been in remission since December 2019. Then 2 months ago I was told I had Bladder cancer. It was removed from my bladder 3 weeks ago and a biopsy carried out on the removed cancer. The results from the biopsy was that I had a High-Grade Papillary Transitional Cell Carcinoma (WHO Grade 3). I have recovered from surgery well and have to wait  another 3 months to see if it comes back and treatment is needed.  Fingers crossed it doesn't return. This is just part of the life us cancer warriors live each and every day worrying if it will return or another cancer will come along. As we all know once you have chemo it increases your chances of getting other cancer( that's what I was told) For now I'm back living a normal life. Cheers”⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER #survivor #cancersurvivor

node.text:
#FCSurvivorSaturday is a day we cherish when we celebrate our warriors that valiantly fought and BEAT cancer🙌🏼. Today we share the story of Tanyce who is 2 years Triple Negative Breast Cancer FREE🙌🏼🙌🏼🙌🏼. Thank you so much Tanyce and husband Russ for sharing your victory with us, you are helping so many find the strength they need to #KEEPFIGHTING. Please leave love in the comments below for warrior Tanyce and her family. Here are some words from her husband 

“Hi, today 8/12/21 my beautiful wife celebrates TWO years TNBC cancer FREE! Without a doubt you are the strongest person I know and the backbone of this family. To be able to go through all the procedures, chemo rounds, radiation that you did and still be the best mother and wife you can be is amazing. I draw inspiration from you everyday! We love you so much and here’s to celebrating you today and everyday! We love you ❤️”

We hope that for anyone that is currently battling that you can find strength and hope from these stories and know that these fighters were once in your same shoes reading someone else’s survivor story wishing and fighting to have their own some day and that YOU too can have that same victory🙏🏽. We hope that you find the inspiration and motivation to #KEEPGOING and #NEVERSTOPFIGHTING 🙌🏼. 
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER #survivor #tnbcsurvivor #tnbc

node.text:
#FxckCancerFriday Today we say🖕🏽🖕🏽 for all those currently in the fight, those that have gone toe to toe and kicked cancer’s ass, those that have lost their battle and for all the loved ones that support and fight along side their warriors we say #FXCKCANCER . 

We thank you all for your daily support in our mission to help spread awareness about prevention and early detection. We also thank every single warrior that has been brave enough to share their journey, fight and strength through their story with us so that we can help others in their same shoes know that they are not going through this alone and to provide hope and faith that they will come out a victor on the other side of cancer 🙌🏼💪🏽. 

#NoOneFightsAlone when it comes to this disease and know that you have this #fxckcancerfamily and community of warriors all in your corner🙏🏽. 

Please leave love for your fighters in the comments below wether it’s for yourself, a friend or a loved one lost and if you have a story you’d like to be feature please DM us it’s our honor to share your strength. 
#TOGETHERWEFIGHT #FXCKCANCER
.
.
.
#Fxckcancer #fuckcancer #fccancerfoundation #fxckcancerfighter #fxckcancersupporter #fxckcancerwarrior #fcancerfoundation #togetherwefight #noonefightsalone #cancerawareness #FXCKCANCER

node.text:
#FCThrowbackThursday featuring our friend and supporter Laura and family celebrating her brother Chiza’s heavenly birthday back in April🙏🏽🤍. #NoOneFightsAlone when is comes to cancer and this was his support system throwing punches along side him throughout his battle🙏🏽. We love this photo and along with this family we keep Chiza in our hearts 🙏🏽.

Who do you fight for?- yourself, a loved one, a friend? Who ever it is give a 🤍 in the comments below for them and some love to our girl Laura and her family.

Thank you for sharing your photos with us, we love seeing them and especially sharing them with our #fxckcancercommunity . Please continue to send them in to us so we can share your light with others who may be in a dark place.🙏🏽
.

We love seeing our #FxckCancerfamily representing with tattoos to permanently show how they feel about cancer and for those that have been impacted.  Whether it’s for themselves, a friend or a loved one, we all can relate. Today we thank Brian Anderson for his permanent support for his friend who is fighting stage 4 lung Cancer and who as pictured started off this tattoo for him🙌🏼. #NoOneFightsAlone and it’s friends and support systems like Brian that our fighters pull strength from to continue in their battle and to beat cancer🙏🏽. 

We thank you Brian for allowing us to share these photos and your friend is in our prayers, we hope to share his survivor story very soon🙏🏽.

node.text:
#FCSurvivorSunday We can’t express enough how much we love sharing your survivor stories and to champion all your victories🙏🏽🙌🏼. Today we celebrate our warrior Leela beating endometrial cancer 🙌🏼🎉. Leela we love your positive attitude and how you advocate for early detection in hopes to help others avoid and prevent cancer. Keep smiling and keep shining and know that we will always be in your corner cheering you on🤍💯. Please leave love for our girl Leela in the comments below.

“I finished my treatments on August 26 2020 and had my CT scan on September 16, 2020. Today, I saw my oncologist and she said there is no evidence of the disease. I know it can come back, but today I am free of cancer and calling that a win. Today i’m saying Fuck Cancer”
.
.
